iscsi script for Xen

Allow automatic using iSCSI targets as disks for domU on Xen/Linux.

For example in your domU Xen script/configuration use:

  disk = [ 'iscsi:iqn.2001-05.com.equallogic:0-8a0906-23fe93404-c82797962054a96d-examplehost,xvda,w' ]

Multipath setup should also be working.

Put in /etc/xen. Configure in block-iscsi.conf

open-iscsi need to be installed.

See http://backdrift.org/xen-block-iscsi-script-with-multipath-support

